INSERT INTO tactic_observations VALUES(1,'2025-26','philosophy','Emery is a pragmatic balance-first coach, not a style idealist: attack-defence balance and meticulous opponent preparation (detailed video analysis) define the model more than any single in-possession identity.','Consistent across profiles; Gerard Moreno (played under Emery): "He is a perfectionist... analyses the opposition to perfection."','https://learning.coachesvoice.com/cv/unai-emery-aston-villa-tactics-style-of-play/ ; https://jobsinfootball.com/blog/unai-emery-tactics-explained/','MEDIUM-HIGH — multiple independent profiles agree; narrative sources.');
INSERT INTO tactic_observations VALUES(2,'2025-26','defence','25/26 defensive foundation is a compact 4-4-2 MID-BLOCK (the 10 rises alongside Watkins; two banks of four), opportunistic ball-winning rather than intense pressing. NOT the ultra-high 23/24 offside-trap line.','Zero counter-attacking goals conceded through mid-season; "prefer to remain compact within their lines of 4-4-2, shuffling with the play". Conflicts with the older high-line narrative — 25/26 sources win for the 25/26 row.','https://themastermindsite.com/2025/12/29/unai-emery-aston-villa-tactical-analysis-2025-26-edition/ ; https://totalfootballanalysis.com/data-analysis/unai-emery-tactics-aston-villa-2025-2026-data-analysis','MEDIUM-HIGH — two 25/26-specific analyses agree; contradicts 23/24-era narrative, conflict recorded here.');
INSERT INTO tactic_observations VALUES(3,'2025-26','build_up','Short build-up from Martínez through the full-backs is a fixed principle — held even when pressed hard ("they often try to play out from the back no matter how well they are being pressed"), occasionally costing turnovers; long outlet to Watkins is the escape valve.','Matches our measured data: Martínez heat centroids on his own goal-line with distribution shifts; Pau Torres BPD carries from LCB.','https://themastermindsite.com/2025/12/29/unai-emery-aston-villa-tactical-analysis-2025-26-edition/ ; appearances 78-80 (Martínez), player_role_map optimal','MEDIUM-HIGH — narrative + our measured GK/CB footprints agree.');
INSERT INTO tactic_observations VALUES(4,'2025-26','in_possession','In possession 4-2-3-1 attacks through CENTRAL numbers and combinations: McGinn and Rogers come inside, Watkins drifts wide/runs behind as the outlet, full-backs advance one at a time (Maatsen through the left half-space), pivot provides cover underneath the ball.','Matches measured heatmaps: Rogers left-inside bias, McGinn right half-space, Buendía left-of-centre No.10 volume (appearances 75-77).','https://themastermindsite.com/2025/12/29/unai-emery-aston-villa-tactical-analysis-2025-26-edition/ ; https://learning.coachesvoice.com/cv/unai-emery-aston-villa-tactics-style-of-play/','MEDIUM-HIGH — narrative + measured coordinates agree.');
INSERT INTO tactic_observations VALUES(5,'2025-26','modulation','Per-match variation happens on FOUR axes while the structure stays fixed: (1) No.10 identity — Rogers central vs Buendía vs Tielemans free-10; (2) Rogers LW inverted (default) vs CAM; (3) second-pivot profile — Onana box-crasher vs Tielemans DLP vs Lindelöf emergency RDM; (4) full-back aggression — Cash defend-first vs overlap, Digne vs Maatsen. Back four + Kamara anchor + Watkins lone ST are near-constants.','Measured from appearances position labels across 39 matches: Konsa RCB-only (5 labels, all RCB), Watkins ST-only, Kamara pivot-only; vs Rogers 7 labels spanning LW/CAM, Tielemans deep-pivot~No.10~sub, Buendía right-hybrid/LM/central-10, Lindelöf CB and RDM.','data/avl_analysis.db appearances (2026-07-02 aggregation)','HIGH for the variation pattern itself (measured from our own per-match records); MEDIUM on completeness (84 appearances ≠ full-season minutes).');
INSERT INTO tactic_observations VALUES(6,'2025-26','verdict','VERDICT — Emery 25/26 is FOUNDATION-FIRST: a fixed structural shell (4-2-3-1↔4-4-2 mid-block, short build-up, central combinations) with per-match modulation done through personnel/role swaps in the attacking band and second pivot, not through changing the game model. Application: ONE base game tactic + role-variant presets sharing identical team settings.','Synthesis of the observations above (scopes: philosophy, defence, build_up, in_possession, modulation).','tactic_observations 1-5','MEDIUM-HIGH — both external analyses ("relatively fixed system") and our measured position-variation data point the same way.');
